  "prompt": "Where can I get free singing lessons via Skype?",
  "response": "There are several resources and platforms where you can find free singing lessons via Skype. Here are some options to consider:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many vocal coaches offer free singing tutorials on their YouTube channels. While not one-on-one lessons, you can learn techniques and practice alongside their videos.\n\n2. **Online Communities**: Websites like Reddit often have communities (subreddits) related to singing where users share resources, including free lessons. Look for subreddits like r/singing.\n\n3. **Vocal Coaches Offering Free Trials**: Some vocal coaches may offer free initial lessons to attract students. You can search for vocal coaches who provide this option, and many advertise their services on social media platforms.\n\n4. **Local Music Schools or Community Centers**: Occasionally, students at music schools looking to gain experience may offer free lessons via video call. Check with local schools or community centers for any outreach programs.\n\n5. **Skill-sharing Platforms**: Websites like Skillshare or Udemy sometimes offer free trials or free courses, which may include singing lessons. Keep an eye out for promotions.\n\n6. **Social Media Platforms**: You might find vocal coaches on platforms like Instagram or TikTok who offer free lessons or demonstrations, and you can reach out to them directly for one-on-one sessions.\n\n7. **Facebook Groups**: Look for singing or vocal training groups on Facebook. Members often share resources or offer to assist each other for free or at a low cost.\n\n8. **Educational Platforms**: Websites like Coursera or edX might offer free courses that include vocal training components.\n\nBe sure to thoroughly vet any instructor or resource you find to ensure quality and professionalism. Happy singing!",
